Job Description:
Degree in Computer Science, Machine Learning, Mathematics etc. (or equivalent experience);
Industry experience with at least one programming language such as Java, Python, C# or C++ and statistical modelling tools, such as R or SAS;
Machine Learning and Data Mining experience to solve business problems;
Functional skills in Computer Science fundamentals (object-oriented design, data structures and algorithms, modelling, information architecture);
Skilled with statistical learning techniques;
Experience working in a cloud environment with distributed workloads and data stores;

Job summary
Are you interested in building the next generation automation and intelligence platform for AWS? We are looking for passionate Machine Learning Engineers like yourself who will help us to build the next generation optimization and matching systems for the paradigm shifting cloud computing industry.

Kumo’s mission is to empower innovators to get the most out of cloud services. We build technology that reimagines how people and automation combine to solve problems, remove risks, build with excellence, and drive business impact. We own critical cloud services used by all AWS customers to build, optimize, and operate at scale. Kumo applications encompass a variety of technical areas such as information retrieval, data mining, big data and machine learning. An example is AWS Trusted Advisor, which performs data mining for customers and gives precise recommendations on cost optimization, security, fault tolerance and performance.

Working with AWS Kumo, you will get first-hand experience interacting across all AWS services such as EC2, S3, RDS, SageMaker, Redshift, DynamoDB and others. You will be surrounded by people who are extremely smart and passionate about cloud computing. Our work has an impact across all AWS customers from Netflix to NASA.

As a Machine Learning Engineer, you’ll develop advanced machine learning models and optimization algorithms for real-world support operations, with the goal of distributing customer requests efficiently to utilize the relative skills of each agent. You’ll collaborate with cross-functional team members, including Software Development Engineers, Data Scientists, System Development Engineers, Business Intelligence Engineers, Applied Scientists and Operations Specialists to create new AI-driven solutions to meet challenging and meaningful problems at enormous scale.

The AWS Kumo team combines the culture of a startup, the innovation and creativity of a R&D Lab, the work-life balance of a mature organization, and technical challenges at the scale of AWS. We offer a playground of opportunities for builders to build and make history!

